    "title": "TOKYO ATTEMPTS TO CALM FRENCH / Foreign Office Declines to Give Assurance on Hainan, but Spokesman Is Soothing (1939)",
    "content": "MENACE TO PEACE DENIED / Japanese Military Forces Take Over Customs at Haikow on Seized Isle TOKYO, Monday, Feb. 13. — French Ambassador Arsene Henry visited Foreign Minister Hachiro Arita at 11:30 this morning in reference to the Japanese occupation of Hainan Island. The Foreign Office declined to make any statement regarding the future of the island, but the spokesman’s remarks this morning seemed intended to allay foreign apprehensions without giving concrete assurances. He quoted Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek’s remark that Japan’s occupation of Hainan was a menace to the peace of the Pacific. “Japan’s occupation of Hainan,” said Tatsuo Kawai, chief of the information section, “has no connection with the peace of the Pacific.” When asked if it was correct to say that Japan had declined to give any assurance regarding the future of Hainan, Mr. Kawai replied that it was premature to say any thing about the future, but added: “Our declaration that Japan has no territorial ambitions in China applies also to Hainan.” The Japanese military forces have taken over the Haikow customs from Commissioner Goldsmith, an American of the Chinese Maritime Customs Service. Mr. Goldsmith was formally notified and replied, according to Domei, Japanese press service, that he took no exception to the Japa- nese action. The transfer to the Japanese military authorities was scheduled for 2 P. M. today. Vice Consul Matsudaira, from Hong Kong, with three consular officials, arrived at Haikow to take charge of diplomatic questions. Figures on the Hainan seizure given out by the Japanese are that 230 Chinese were killed on Friday, while the Japanese reported three killed and two wounded. New York Times, February 13, 1939 否認對和平構成威脅 / 日本軍方接管被占領島嶼海口的海關 東京，2月13日，星期一 — — 今天上午11點30分，法國大使阿爾塞納·亨利拜訪了外務大臣有田八郎，討論日本佔領海南島的問題。 外務省拒絕就該島的未來發表任何聲明，但今天上午發言人的言論似乎旨在緩解外國的擔憂，同時未作出具體保證。他引用了蔣介石總司令的評論，稱日本佔領海南島是對太平洋和平的威脅。 情報科主任河相達夫說：「日本佔領海南島與太平洋的和平無關。」 當被問及日本是否拒絕就海南島的未來作出任何保證是否正確時，河相先生回答說，現在談論未來還為時過早，但他補充道：「我們聲明日本在中國沒有領土野心，這一點也適用於海南島。」 日本軍事力量已從中國海關總稅務司的美國人戈德史密斯手中接管了海口海關。 據日本通訊社同盟通訊報導，戈德史密斯先生收到正式通知後回覆說，他對日本的行動沒有異議。移交給日本軍事當局的時間定於今天下午2點。 來自香港的副領事松平與三名領事官員抵達海口，負責處理外交事務。 日本方面提供的海南島奪取數據顯示，週五有230名中國人被殺，而日方報告有3人死亡、2人受傷。 《紐約時報》，1939年2月13日",
